            <p class="nds-card-description nds-truncate" style="--truncate:4;">The Social Responsibility Department serves as a key representative of community service and the university&#x2019;s third mission. It places the delivery of distinguished community services among its highest priorities, reflecting the university&#x2019;s excellence through its programs, objectives, and aspirations. The department seeks to establish effective strategic partnerships through the services it provides to local and international communities, in alignment with the university&#x2019;s vision and mission.The Islamic University was established by Royal Decree No. 11 dated 25/3/1381 AH, followed by Royal Decree No. 21 dated 16/4/1381 AH, to serve as a leading global Islamic beacon of knowledge and development.Subsequently, approval was granted for the establishment of the Deanship of Community Service at the university pursuant to Ministerial Decision No. 8/2 dated 11/6/1416 AH.Based on the Decision of the Council of University Affairs No. (1443/6/12) dated 13/9/1443 AH, and the Decision of the President of the Islamic University No. 91444440 dated 09/01/1444 AH, the Deanship of Community Service was transformed into the General Directorate of Community Service.Later, pursuant to Administrative Decision No. 9144711748 dated 15/04/1447 AH, the President of the Islamic University issued Decision No. 9144720507 dated 19/06/1447 AH, renaming the General Directorate of Community Service as the Social Responsibility Department, affiliated with the University&#x2019;s Office of International Cooperation and Partnerships.</p>
